        <p>Lexicographer. Taught English in Paris. Worked for fourteen years on his <hi rend="italic">General English and French dictionary</hi> (1846); awarded a PhD for it by the University of Giessen, 1849. An abridged version, <hi rend="italic">Dictionnaire abrégé anglais–français</hi>, was published in 1851 and was widely used in French schools.</p></note>
